      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/31/13",
      "text": [
        ": سَأَلْتُهُ عَنْ عَلاَمَةِ لَيْلَةِ اَلْقَدْرِ فَقَالَ «عَلاَمَتُهَا أَنْ تَطِيبَ رِيحُهَا وَ إِنْ كَانَتْ فِي بَرْدٍ دَفِئَتْ وَ إِنْ كَانَتْ فِي حَرٍّ بَرَدَتْ وَ طَابَتْ»."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2027 - It is narrated from Al-Ala from Muhammad ibn Muslim, who narrated from one of the two (Imam Al-Baqir (as) or Imam Al-Sadiq (as), peace be upon them), who said: \"I asked him about the sign of Laylatul Qadr, and Imam (as) replied:\n'Its sign is that its breeze is pleasant; if it is in cold weather, it becomes warm, and if it is in hot weather, it becomes cool and pleasant.'\""
        ]
      }
    },
